Starring: Robert De Niro, Cybill Shepherd, Peter Boyle, Jodie Foster 
Director: Martin Scorsese
Studio: Columbia Pictures
Genre: Drama / Thriller / Crime
Release Date: February 8, 1976
Run Time: 110 min 
SYNOPSIS:
At 26, Vietnam veteran Travis Bickle (De Niro) is slipping slowly into 
isolation and violence on the streets of New York City. Trying to solve 
his insomnia by driving a yellow cab on the night shift, he grows 
increasingly disgusted by the people who hang out at night: ?Someday 
a real rain will come and wash all the scum off the streets.? His touching 
attempts to woo Betsy (Cybill Shepherd), a Senator's campaign worker, turn 
sour when he takes her to a porn movie on their first date. He even fails 
in his attempt to persuade child prostitute Iris (Jodie Foster) to desert 
her pimp Sport (Harvey Keitel) and return to her parents and school. Driven 
to the edge by powerlessness, he buys four handguns and sets out to 
assassinate the Senator, heading for the infamy of a `lone crazed gunman'.
